data.enText: a thing that is added to sth else to improve or complete it

data.chText: 补充的维生素；补充饮食
data.enText: vitamin/dietary supplements (= vitamins and other foods eaten in addition to what you usually eat)

data.chText: 工业界的赞助是对政府拨款的补充。
data.enText: Industrial sponsorship is a supplement to government funding.
an extra separate section, often in the form of a magazine, that is sold with a newspaper
a book or a section at the end of a book that gives extra information or deals with a special subject
the supplement to the Oxford English Dictionary

data.chText: 额外费用，附加费（尤指度假服务的）
data.enText: an amount of money that you pay for an extra service or item, especially in addition to the basic cost of a holiday/vacation
There is a £10 supplement for a single room.

data.chText: 有贵重物品保管箱可供使用，费用另计。
data.enText: Safety deposit boxes are available at a supplement .
to add sth to sth in order to improve it or make it more complete

data.chText: 搭配有维生素片的饮食
data.enText: a diet supplemented with vitamin pills

data.chText: 他当家庭教师以补充收入。
data.enText: He supplements his income by giving private lessons.

simple_means.memory_skill: sup 下 + ple 满的；填满 + ment 表名词 → 从下面增加以填满 → 补充

ex.chText: 小宝宝的到来为她的家庭增添了喜悦。
ex.enText: The baby is a happy addition to her family.

ex.chText: 这是该公司汽车系列的新增款式。
ex.enText: This is the latest addition to the company's range of automobiles.

synonyms.bx: 指数量的增加，表示从属于整体的增加部分。

ex.chText: 相机要是带有闪光灯的话，我们晚上也可以拍照了。
ex.enText: With a flash-bulb attachment, we could also take pictures at night.
The electric drill has various attachments.

synonyms.bx: 指附属物，主要用于增加主体的用途。

ex.chText: 其他膳食补充剂包括什么？
ex.enText: What do the other dietary supplements include?

ex.chText: 这些款项是她日常工资的补贴吗？
ex.enText: Are these payments a supplement to her usual salary?

synonyms.bx: 指补充物或使报纸、杂志等完善而增加的部分。

tr: a supplementary component that improves capability
a quantity added (e.g. to make up for a deficiency)
textual matter that is added onto a publication

example: He appended a glossary to his novel where he used an invented language

tr: add as a supplement to what seems insufficient

value.def: If you supplement something, you add something to it in order to improve it.

example.ex: ...people doing extra jobs outside their regular jobs to supplement their incomes...
example.tran: 除了正常的工作外还要额外兼职以贴补收入的人

example.ex: I suggest supplementing your diet with vitamins E and A.
example.tran: 我建议你在日常饮食中补充些维生素 E 和维生素 A。

example.ex: Business sponsorship must be a supplement to, not a substitute for, public funding.
example.tran: 商业赞助必须是公共基金的一种补充，而不能取而代之。

value.def: A supplement is a pill that you take or a special kind of food that you eat in order to improve your health.

example.tran: 含复合维生素和矿物质的营养剂

example.ex: I took regular supplements and exercised every day.
example.tran: 我每天都按时吃营养片并坚持锻炼。

value.def: A supplement is a separate part of a magazine or newspaper, often dealing with a particular topic.

example.ex: ...a special supplement to a monthly financial magazine.
example.tran: 一本金融杂志月刊的特别增刊

value.def: A supplement to a book is an additional section, written some time after the main text and published either at the end of the book or separately.
A supplement is an extra amount of money that you pay in order to obtain special facilities or services, for example when you are travelling or staying at a hotel.

example.ex: If you are travelling alone, the single room supplement is £11 a night.
example.tran: 如果是一个人旅行，住单间每晚要多交 11 英镑。

value.def: A supplement is an extra amount of money that is paid to someone, in addition to their normal pension or income.

example.ex: Some people may be entitled to a housing benefit supplement.
example.tran: 有些人可能有资格拿到住房补贴。

example.ex: ...people who need a supplement to their basic pension.
example.tran: 除了基本养老金外还需要额外补贴的人

rootsaffixes.title: ple, plen(t), plet

partsOfSpeech.dec: com 加强 + ple 满的；填满 + ment 表名词 → 都填满了 → 补足
com 加强 + plet 满的；填满 + e → 特别满 → 完全的
com 加强 + ple 满的；填满 + tion 表名词 → 都填满 → 圆满
de 否定，非 + plen 满的；填满 + ish 使… → 使不满 → 倒空
im 使… + ple 满的；填满 + ment 结果 → 使圆满 → 实现
plent 满的；填满 + itude 表状态 → 满的状态 → 丰富
plen 满的；填满 + ty 表状态 → 大量，丰富
re 重新 + plen 满的；填满 + ish 使… → 重新装满 → 再装满
re 一再 + plet 满的；填满 + e → 一再填满〔肚子、容器等的〕→ 充满的；吃饱的
sup 下 + ple 满的；填满 + ment 表名词 → 从下面增加以填满 → 补充
